  "prompt": "How is the movie \"Happy New Year\"?",
  "response": "\"Happy New Year,\" released in 2014, is a Bollywood heist film directed by Farah Khan and features an ensemble cast including Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone, Abhishek Bachchan, and Boman Irani. The story revolves around a group of misfits who come together to pull off a major heist during a dance competition in Dubai.\n\nThe movie combines elements of comedy, action, and drama, with a heavy emphasis on dance and music, characteristic of Farah Khan's filmmaking style. While the film received mixed to negative reviews from critics, it was commercially successful, largely due to the star power of its lead actors and its entertaining music.\n\nViewers praised the movie for its lavish production, catchy songs, and dance sequences, while some criticized its lengthy run time and predictable plot. Overall, \"Happy New Year\" is known for its light-hearted approach and family-friendly entertainment, making it a fun watch for fans of Bollywood cinema. If you're looking for a feel-good movie with a mix of comedy and action, it could be worth watching.",
